Name:
shielded-plains-71844.herokuapp.com

Push to heroku:
git push heroku master

Deploy with DB:
1. Create clearDB database:
heroku addons:create cleardb:ignite

2. Get database URL:
heroku config | grep CLEARDB_DATABASE_URL
Copy from mysql://...

5. Set database:
heroku config:set DATABASE_URL='mysql://bd541b76d1cb87:86e2719f@us-cdbr-iron-east-04.cleardb.net/heroku_3a8a7d70d740947?reconnect=true'

6. Update config info in repo to connect to heroku db:
const connection = mysql.createConnection({
    username: "bd541b76d1cb87",
    password: "86e2719f",
    host: "us-cdbr-iron-east-04.cleardb.net",
    database: "heroku_3a8a7d70d740947"
});

7. Create connection to remote db in mysql and supply schema / seed data...
use heroku_3a8a7d70d740947;
create table... etc.

8. Check status of dynos in heroku cli:
heroku ps

9. Restart specific dyno:
heroku ps:restart web.1

(See https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/dynos for more CLI commands)


